                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "t40Bqf",
              "width": 720,
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "DwBuI",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 1.5,
                  "height": 9
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "FTQL3",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 48,
                  "height": 1.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "fHKro",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 1.5,
                  "height": 9
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "OqhN3",
              "width": 720,
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 22,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "szUMv",
                  "fill": "$inkMuted",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In the intricate dance of code reviews, there’s a common pitfall that many senior developers and tech leads encounter: the tendency to drop subtle hints rather than providing clear, actionable feedback. While the intention might be to foster independence, this approach can often lead to more confusion than growth.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "UAN9Z",
                  "fill": "$ink",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The problem with vague feedback",
                  "lineHeight": 1.25,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 26,
                  "fontWeight": "600"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "QYDUD",
                  "fill": "$inkMuted",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "When a code review is filled with hints like “this could be optimized” or “consider a different approach here” without further explanation, it leaves the developer guessing. They might not fully understand what needs to change or why a different approach is better. This can lead to frustration, repeated mistakes, and a slower learning process.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "M149A",
                  "fill": "$ink",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The power of clarity",
                  "lineHeight": 1.25,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 26,
                  "fontWeight": "600"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "KFUnT",
                  "fill": "$inkMuted",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Clear, specific feedback is a powerful tool for growth. When a reviewer explains not only what needs to change but also why, it helps the developer understand the reasoning behind the decision. This not only resolves the immediate issue but also equips the developer with knowledge they can apply in the future.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "UmYd1",
                  "fill": "$ink",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Fostering a supportive code review culture",
                  "lineHeight": 1.25,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 26,
                  "fontWeight": "600"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Vbnmq",
                  "fill": "$inkMuted",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "A supportive code review culture is built on open communication and trust. When developers feel that their reviewers are invested in their growth and success, they’re more likely to engage in meaningful dialogue and embrace feedback. This creates a more collaborative and productive environment, where everyone is continuously learning and improving together.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "YaOO5",
                  "fill": "$inkMuted",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In the end, the goal of code reviews isn’t just to catch bugs or enforce standards—it’s to help each developer grow and become more confident in their craft. By moving away from vague hints and towards clear, constructive feedback, we can create a more supportive and effective development environment for everyone.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
