          "gap": 18,
          "padding": [
            28,
            20,
            40,
            20
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "m5NsC",
              "gap": 10,
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "K1uQN",
                  "fill": "$inkFaint",
                  "content": "Aug 6, 2025",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "BfzqV",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "content": "Leadership · Craft",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "b6bg2m",
              "fill": "$ink",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Clarity Leads to Growth: Why Vague Hints in Code Reviews Can Be Counterproductive",
              "lineHeight": 1.2,
              "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
              "fontSize": 26,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "vk06J",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Vague hints slow growth. Clear, specific feedback helps developers learn faster, avoid repeat mistakes, and build confidence.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "fejU8",
              "fill": "$inkFaint",
              "content": "Jason Rundell · Player-Coach",
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "jaJsO",
              "padding": [
                4,
                0
              ],
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "u9jeW6",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 1.5,
                  "height": 8
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "u0hqZR",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 36,
                  "height": 1.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "jSK50",
                  "fill": "$accent",
                  "width": 1.5,
                  "height": 8
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "n3lUP",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "In the intricate dance of code reviews, there’s a common pitfall: dropping subtle hints rather than clear, actionable feedback. The intention might be independence - the result is often confusion.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "w3JcWr",
              "fill": "$ink",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The problem with vague feedback",
              "lineHeight": 1.25,
              "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "OkvC7",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Hints like “this could be optimized” leave the developer guessing. Without the why, they repeat mistakes and learn slower.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "zzMEe",
              "fill": "$ink",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The power of clarity",
              "lineHeight": 1.25,
              "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "r71wv",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "When a reviewer explains what needs to change and why, the developer internalizes the practice - not just the patch.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "YQCLA",
              "fill": "$ink",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Fostering a supportive culture",
              "lineHeight": 1.25,
              "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "BT8fB",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Trust grows when reviewers invest in growth. Clear feedback builds a collaborative environment where everyone keeps learning.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "MW19Q",
              "fill": "$inkMuted",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The goal of code reviews isn’t just catching bugs - it’s helping each developer grow more confident in their craft.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "al4Hp",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "stroke": "$lineSubtle",
              "strokeWidth": {
                "top": 1
              },
